## Testing plan

All three gates run: `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `build` gate: `OpticalConstructor.Ui` compiles with the seven `Charts/*.fs` modules against the public MIT Avalonia/FuncUI/ScottPlot/Plotly.NET/WebView2 NuGet packages; no reference to the FuncUI clone.
- `constructor-unit-tests` gate (hosted in `OpticalConstructor.Tests`, the single gated host — reconciler round-2 §g, no separate project): the four new test files pass and increase the count over the prior baseline.
  - AC-H1/AC-H3 (SeriesDataTests): 1D adapter over `calculate` reproduces the `(x,y)` pairs `Charting.plot` would choose; surface adapter Z grid equals `mapFun` output for a fixed `calculate3D` run.
  - AC-H6 (ReadoutTests): peak finder returns the apex, min finder the trough, FWHM the half-max width, two-cursor delta the exact ΔX/ΔY — purely over the `SeriesData` array, no re-solve.
  - AC-H4/AC-H5 (ChartSettingsTests): `applyToScottPlot`/`applyToPlotly` omit `visible=false` traces and apply `Log10`; an nm→eV axis-unit switch routes through the §A.10 boundary conversion and the stored series/`ChartSettings` remain canonical SI.
  - AC-H7 (PolarizationPlotTests): for a known reflected `EmFieldSystem`, ellipse curve parameters match `ellipticityR`/`azimuthR` and the Poincaré point equals normalized `Solution.stokesR`.
- AC-H2/AC-H8/AC-H9/AC-H10 are covered at the adapter/view boundary: overlay reuses `plotComparison`'s layout with no `Chart.show`; field-depth consumes §F.6 `fieldDepthProfile`; CIE consumes the §F.8 `{ x; y; rgb }`; dispersion adapts `plotDispersion`/`plotN11`…`plotRho33` to renderer-neutral arrays with no `Chart.show`.
- `unit-tests` gate (BerremanTests) stays green (not touched here).

## Risks

- **Medium.** This slice is wide (seven view modules, two renderers) but thin per file because the data path is reused, not re-invented. The load-bearing risks: (1) re-running the solver inside a view instead of consuming `SeriesData` (forbidden by §H.2/§H.7 — keep views pure functions of series + `ChartSettings`); (2) calling the engine's terminal `Chart.show` and opening a browser tab (forbidden by §H.2/§H.4/§H.11 — reuse only the series-assembly bodies); (3) drifting from the slice-001 buildable FuncUI interpretation and reintroducing the audit-gated clone or an OpenTK path into charts (forbidden — Plot3DView is Plotly, §H.5). Mitigation: prove the adapter equivalence and the projection/omit behaviour by unit test, and keep every renderer behind `applyToScottPlot`/`applyToPlotly`.

## Hand-off

The chart layer exists and is unit-tested: one immutable `ChartSettings` (the §A.7 chart-settings slot) with the sole `applyToScottPlot`/`applyToPlotly` projections; the renderer-neutral `SeriesData` adapter over the Part A sweeps seam; the ScottPlot 1D/overlay/field-depth/dispersion view, the Plotly-in-WebView2 surface view, the readout tools, the polarization ellipse + Poincaré sphere, and the CIE view. The slice consumes Part F (slice 008) for §F.6 field-depth and §F.8 color, and produces the `ChartHandle`/series that Part I §I.7 (slice 013) exports. The buildable FuncUI interpretation (public MIT NuGet; clone stays audit-gated, linking unresolved) is preserved. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
